26
00:03:57.370 --> 00:04:01.569
MAN: The state of Montana
has never gauged its progress

27
00:04:01.641 --> 00:04:04.543
by the size of its cities.

28
00:04:04.611 --> 00:04:06.705
We measure our progress

29
00:04:06.780 --> 00:04:08.806
by how those cities
impact the people

30
00:04:08.915 --> 00:04:10.975
and the land surrounding them.

31
00:04:11.084 --> 00:04:12.643
the land that feeds them.

32
00:04:12.786 --> 00:04:15.756
provides their water.
nourishes their souls.

33
00:04:16.056 --> 00:04:18.423
MAN 2: This doesn't sound
like a legal argument. Mr. Dutton.

34
00:04:18.525 --> 00:04:20.289
It sounds like a lecture.

35
00:04:20.393 --> 00:04:22.338
MAN: Well. it's a summation
of our state constitution.

36
00:04:22.362 --> 00:04:24.040
which clearly states
that land preservation

37
00:04:24.064 --> 00:04:27.091
and property rights take
precedence over public expansion.

38
00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:30.965
The constitution clearly denotes
the state's right to eminent domain

39
00:04:31.071 --> 00:04:33.165
and grants the authority
to condemn property

40
00:04:33.273 --> 00:04:34.400
for the public good.

41
00:04:34.541 --> 00:04:36.066
For essential public services

42
00:04:36.143 --> 00:04:39.739
like hospitals. schools. highways.
not housing developments.

43
00:04:39.846 --> 00:04:41.576
Housing is essential.

44
00:04:42.482 --> 00:04:45.179
Bozeman has doubled
in size in a decade.

45
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:47.015
We're 30 miles away.

46
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:51.114
and our population is less
than it was 40 years ago.

47
00:04:51.191 --> 00:04:55.094
Why? Because their fence
guarantees we don't grow.

48
00:04:55.829 --> 00:04:57.593
Stagnation is death for a town.

49
00:04:57.664 --> 00:04:59.633
