00:17:02.321 --> 00:17:04.085
(CHANTING AND
DRUMMING CONTINUES)

253
00:17:04.323 --> 00:17:06.224
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

254
00:17:06.325 --> 00:17:09.227
(CHANTING AND DRUMMING
CONTINUES IN DISTANCE)

255
00:17:12.665 --> 00:17:14.759
Senator.

256
00:17:14.867 --> 00:17:16.335
I'm sorry I'm late.

257
00:17:16.402 --> 00:17:18.371
I wanted to see
the reservation first.

258
00:17:18.437 --> 00:17:19.996
Did you enjoy your tour?

259
00:17:20.072 --> 00:17:22.234
No. no. I did not.

260
00:17:22.341 --> 00:17:24.572
Well. it's good
that you took it.

261
00:17:24.677 --> 00:17:27.169
Inequity must be
witnessed to be changed.

262
00:17:27.413 --> 00:17:29.382
Please have a seat.

263
00:17:29.448 --> 00:17:30.916
Oh.

264
00:17:32.385 --> 00:17:35.719
I can't imagine all your mother
overcame just to raise you here.

265
00:17:36.455 --> 00:17:39.550
I never met my mother.
and I wasn't raised here.

266
00:17:39.625 --> 00:17:41.856
Till I was 18. I
thought I was Mexican

267
00:17:42.428 --> 00:17:44.056
even though I
didn't look Mexican

268
00:17:44.297 --> 00:17:46.198
and I didn't feel Mexican.

269
00:17:46.265 --> 00:17:49.064
if one can feel their heritage.
which I believe one can.

270
00:17:49.769 --> 00:17:52.432
When I turned 18. my
adoption records were unsealed.

271
00:17:53.439 --> 00:17:54.634
and imagine my surprise.

272
00:17:55.741 --> 00:18:00.441
I confronted my adopted parents.
who said they lied to protect me.

273
00:18:02.748 --> 00:18:03.875
They said as a Mexican.

274
00:18:05.084 --> 00:18:07.451
I would face
discrimination. sure.

275
00:18:08.921 --> 00:18:11.948
but as an Indian. I
would know a hatred

276
00:18:12.758 --> 00:18:15.193
that had to be endured
to be fully understood.

277
00:18:16.395 --> 00:18:19.229
They thought they were
giving me a better chance at life.

278
00:18:20.066 --> 00:18:25.300
That's this nation's policy
toward us. always has been.

279
00:18:25.404 --> 00:18:30.468
If we want a better life. all we
have to do is stop being Indian.

280
00:18:30.576 --> 00:18:32.807
I'm gonna change that policy.

281
00:18:32.912 --> 00:18:35.643
My people are the only ones
that can change that policy.

282
00:18:38.284 --> 00:18:40.253
(SIGHS)

283
00:18:40.319 --> 00:18:42.481
The gambler's
money is like a river.

284
00:18:43.089 --> 00:18:46.150
flowing one way. our way.

285
00:18:46.926 --> 00:18:49.293
Senator. you've
never driven a road

286
00:18:49.362 --> 00:18:52.491
or walked a trail or skied
a mountain in Montana

287
00:18:52.598 --> 00:18:55.932
that didn't belong
to my people first.

288
00:18:56.002 --> 00:18:58.801
This nation doesn't
want to give it back?

289
00:18:58.871 --> 00:19:00.669
So be it.

290
00:19:00.773 --> 00:19:03.504
We'll buy it back

291
00:19:03.609 --> 00:19:05.077
with their money.

292
00:19:05.144 --> 00:19:06.976
So what do you want from me?

293
00:19:09.348 --> 00:19:11.510
I want you to help me spend it.

294
00:19:13.119 --> 00:19:16.317
Come. Meet the
people we're saving.

295
00:19:18.991 --> 00:19:21.620
MAN: (ON MEGAPHONE) <i>Ladies
and gentlemen. let's welcome</i>

296
00:19:21.794 --> 00:19:27.358
<i>the new chairman of Broken
Rock. Thomas Rainwater!</i>

297
00:19:27.566 --> 00:19:30.365
(CHEERING AND APPLAUDING)

298
00:19:33.839 --> 00:19:35.467
What about water and power?

299
00:19:35.541 --> 00:19:37.806
You don't need
a permit for that?

300
00:19:37.877 --> 00:19:40.711
See. the bank's concern is
that you're gonna break ground.

301
00:19:40.813 --> 00:19:44.511
and the state or the fucking
EPA paper us in lawsuits

302
00:19:44.583 --> 00:19:47.314
because we built a power
plant without a permit.

303
00:19:47.520 --> 00:19:49.716
In the state of Montana.
no permit is required

304
00:19:49.822 --> 00:19:52.485
to build a power source
for a mine or a mill.

305
00:19:52.825 --> 00:19:54.817
Now. we'll construct
our own mill

306
00:19:54.894 --> 00:19:58.763
that will also allow us to harvest
wood directly from the forest.

307
00:19:59.598 --> 00:20:02.932
cutting our lumber cost by 65%.

308
00:20:05.304 --> 00:20:08.035
Damming the river here
will generate enough power

309
00:20:08.107 --> 00:20:10.076
to light every home
in the subdivision.

310
00:20:10.176 --> 00:20:12.771
Now. this is a
self-sustaining community

311
00:20:12.878 --> 00:20:17.748
thirty miles from the most pristine
wilderness in North America.

312
00:20:17.850 --> 00:20:20.376
Now. if you don't see
the potential in that.

313
00:20:20.453 --> 00:20:22.854
- we need another bank.
- We see the potential.

314
00:20:22.922 --> 00:20:24.322
I just...

315
00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:27.519
There are no restrictions
on damming a river?

316
00:20:28.227 --> 00:20:30.196
Beavers do it all the time.

317
00:20:30.262 --> 00:20:32.959
On our land it's our river.

318
00:20:33.065 --> 00:20:34.897
Now. this isn't
California. gentlemen.

319
00:20:35.601 --> 00:20:37.331
This is Montana.

320
00:20:40.206 --> 00:20:42.334
We can do whatever we want.

321
00:20:43.542 --> 00:20:45.443
- (CAR DOOR THUDS)
- (ENGINE TURNS OVER)

322
00:20:47.713 --> 00:20:50.615
(SOFT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING IN BAR)

323
00:21:10.236 --> 00:21:12.603
My name's Ted.
Where are you from?

324
00:21:14.640 --> 00:21:16.165
Really? (LAUGHS)

325
00:21:16.308 --> 00:21:17.401
I've been here a week.

326
00:21:17.476 --> 00:21:20.412
You're the first person I've
met who's actually from here.

327
00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:23.306
Can I buy you another drink?

328
00:21:23.415 --> 00:21:24.644
Why not?

329
00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:27.811
Hey. Dalton. give
me another one.

330
00:21:28.120 --> 00:21:30.919
You don't live here anymore.
though. not dressed like that.

331
00:21:31.390 --> 00:21:33.791
You came back
for a family reunion.

332
00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:37.120
No. no. those never happen
at home for some reason.

333
00:21:38.030 --> 00:21:41.467
Let's see. Bozeman
is a college town.

334
00:21:42.401 --> 00:21:45.462
so I'm gonna say
a school reunion.

335
00:21:45.704 --> 00:21:49.436
class of 2006.

336
00:21:50.676 --> 00:21:52.201
Am I close?

337
00:21:53.712 --> 00:21:55.146
Do you feel close. Ted?

338
00:21:56.182 --> 00:21:57.946
Ah. it feels like
I'm getting close.

339
00:21:58.684 --> 00:22:00.380
My turn.

340
00:22:01.654 --> 00:22:04.488
You're in real estate or
something equally as unimportant.

341
00:22:04.623 --> 00:22:06.785
married. couple of
kids. one on the way.

342
00:22:06.859 --> 00:22:09.294
That was your excuse
to come out here.

343
00:22:09.361 --> 00:22:11.523
Need the break.
Work. family life.

344
00:22:11.630 --> 00:22:13.326
It's so demanding.

345
00:22:13.399 --> 00:22:16.233
A little fresh air.
a little "me time."

346
00:22:16.502 --> 00:22:18.822
You came alone 'cause none
of your friends could afford it.

347
00:22:18.871 --> 00:22:20.499
and those who do.
they... They have wives

348
00:22:20.606 --> 00:22:22.484
a lot smarter than yours
'cause let's be honest. Ted.

349
00:22:22.508 --> 00:22:24.636
you didn't come here to fish.

350
00:22:24.710 --> 00:22:26.144
You're hunting.

351
00:22:26.212 --> 00:22:29.205
That's why you're sitting in a
bar instead of standing in a river.

352
00:22:31.183 --> 00:22:32.708
Who the hell are
you to judge me?

353
00:22:32.818 --> 00:22:34.548
I ain't judging you. buddy.

354
00:22:34.887 --> 00:22:35.887
Morning. gentlemen.

355
00:22:36.222 --> 00:22:39.317
I'm hunting too.
just not hunting you.

356
00:22:40.059 --> 00:22:41.493
What's wrong with me?

357
00:22:42.862 --> 00:22:45.161
You look like a
real soft fuck. Ted.

358
00:22:46.398 --> 00:22:48.026
All you city boys do.

359
00:22:53.505 --> 00:22:55.997
Gentlemen. mind if I join you?

360
00:22:56.175 --> 00:22:58.041
(RANCHERS SHOUTING)

361
00:22:58.177 --> 00:23:01.079
RANCHER: They even got
the barbed wire tore down.

362
00:23:01.213 --> 00:23:03.341
That is our property.
God damn it.

363
00:23:03.415 --> 00:23:04.883
Can't hear ya.

364
00:23:04.950 --> 00:23:06.748
Come about two feet closer.

365
00:23:06.852 --> 00:23:09.083
- You think I won't?
- I think you shouldn't.

366
00:23:09.188 --> 00:23:11.282
but coming on our land
is bred into you people.

367
00:23:12.024 --> 00:23:13.959
I've had enough of your shit.

368
00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:16.426
Let me tell you something...

369
00:23:17.396 --> 00:23:19.365
- (MEN SHOUTING)
- (GUNS CLICKING)

370
00:23:19.431 --> 00:23:21.525
When those cattle
walked onto our land.

371
00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:24.297
they became our cattle
to do as we please.

372
00:23:24.403 --> 00:23:27.305
Whatever happens
next happens to you first.

373
00:23:27.406 --> 00:23:30.069
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

374
00:23:31.610 --> 00:23:33.078
Son of a bitch.

375
00:23:37.249 --> 00:23:38.444
Back up.

376
00:23:38.550 --> 00:23:40.143
You should respect
your veterans.

377
00:23:59.471 --> 00:24:01.167
Boy. you sure
made a mess of this.

378
00:24:01.273 --> 00:24:02.764
It was a mess when I got here.

379
00:24:04.143 --> 00:24:05.975
This is a tribal issue. John.

380
00:24:06.078 --> 00:24:07.689
Livestock commission's
got no authority here.

381
00:24:07.713 --> 00:24:09.944
Those look like livestock to me.

382
00:24:10.883 --> 00:24:14.650
The Chief's at Commencement.
but I'm calling the shots.

383
00:24:16.155 --> 00:24:18.989
I'm impressed you said
that with a straight face. Ben.

384
00:24:23.462 --> 00:24:26.489
The cattle wandered
onto res land. John.

385
00:24:26.598 --> 00:24:28.260
Yeah. well.

386
00:24:28.334 --> 00:24:30.769
cattle don't know the difference
between your land and ours.

387
00:24:30.836 --> 00:24:33.931
Neither did we till the
government showed us. Ha.

388
00:24:34.440 --> 00:24:36.671
Now I guess we're showing you.

389
00:24:38.110 --> 00:24:41.478
I argued against it.
but the new chief...

390
00:24:42.815 --> 00:24:44.477
Hungry for a fight. this one.

391
00:24:45.351 --> 00:24:47.047
God damn it. I just...

392
00:24:48.954 --> 00:24:51.822
I just don't see how anyone
gains from all this. Felix.

393
00:24:51.924 --> 00:24:55.053
I don't either. but
he don't think like me.

394
00:24:56.195 --> 00:25:00.155
Grew up in Denver. went
to some big university.

395
00:25:01.667 --> 00:25:03.533
Now he thinks like you.

396
00:25:13.178 --> 00:25:16.046
I'll keep 'em here as
long as I can. John.

397
00:25:19.051 --> 00:25:21.418
I'll bring up hay so
they don't wander.

398
00:25:25.224 --> 00:25:27.318
- Lee!
- I got to go.

399
00:25:28.827 --> 00:25:30.352
Clear everyone out.

400
00:25:32.364 --> 00:25:34.890
You know. there was barbed
wire on this fence a week ago.

401
00:25:38.003 --> 00:25:39.995
I know. Now clear them out.

402
00:25:41.040 --> 00:25:43.009
RANCHER: Move out!
JOHN: All right. let's go!

403
00:25:43.075 --> 00:25:46.204
GIRL: (SINGING)
<i>Our flag was still there</i>

404
00:25:47.046 --> 00:25:52.542
<i>Oh. say does that star-spangled</i>

405
00:25:52.618 --> 00:25:58.285
<i>Banner yet wave</i>

406
00:25:58.390 --> 00:26:04.694
<i>O'er the land of the free</i>

407
00:26:04.763 --> 00:26:11.135
<i>And the home of the brave</i>

408
00:26:11.236 --> 00:26:14.035
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

409
00:26:17.476 --> 00:26:19.254
AUCTIONEER: <i>Ladies and
gentlemen. I'd like to welcome you out</i>

410
00:26:19.278 --> 00:26:20.940
<i>to the 2018</i>

411
00:26:21.046 --> 00:26:23.038
<i>Greater Montana
Livestock Auction.</i>

412
00:26:23.115 --> 00:26:24.879
<i>We're gonna start out
with lot number one.</i>

413
00:26:24.950 --> 00:26:27.943
<i>It's Royal M. Duke.
a 2013 registered</i>

414
00:26:28.053 --> 00:26:30.579
<i>English bull offered by
Double G Angus Ranch.</i>

415
00:26:30.656 --> 00:26:34.593
<i>sired by Supreme
Domino out of Miss Domino.</i>

416
00:26:34.660 --> 00:26:36.788
<i>Now we're gonna start
the bidding out at 25.000.</i>

417
00:26:36.895 --> 00:26:39.888
<i>I'm at 25. I'm at 50.</i>
(AUCTIONEERING)

418
00:26:39.965 --> 00:26:41.627
<i>I'm at 55. gonna
go 60. at 60 now.</i>

419
00:26:41.733 --> 00:26:44.498
<i>now five on 65.000.
65 looking for 70.</i>

420
00:26:44.603 --> 00:26:47.801
(AUCTIONEERING) <i>Seventy-five.
75. and now bid at 80. 80.000. 85?</i>

421
00:26:47.906 --> 00:26:48.965
Eighty-five now 90. 90?

422
00:26:49.241 --> 00:26:51.574
Just gotta make one
phone call. I'll be right back.

423
00:26:54.146 --> 00:26:58.481
We have any legal
recourse on reservation land?

424
00:26:58.584 --> 00:27:01.110
Civil maybe. but if
you're talking prosecution.

425
00:27:01.220 --> 00:27:03.451
we need friends in the
US Attorney's Office.

426
00:27:05.958 --> 00:27:07.085
Make some.

427
00:27:07.259 --> 00:27:08.420
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

428
00:27:08.927 --> 00:27:10.520
Hello. Trent.

429
00:27:10.929 --> 00:27:12.158
John.

430
00:27:12.965 --> 00:27:15.525
I wouldn't wish the week you're
having on my mother-in-law.

431
00:27:15.834 --> 00:27:18.702
- (LAUGHING)
- Well. it's only Tuesday.

432
00:27:20.139 --> 00:27:21.232
<i>Fifty. 60. 60.</i>

433
00:27:21.306 --> 00:27:22.433
<i>Now 70. Seventy now.</i>

434
00:27:22.508 --> 00:27:24.238
<i>Seventy-five. now bid at 80. 80.</i>

435
00:27:24.309 --> 00:27:25.470
John.

436
00:27:27.279 --> 00:27:28.804
This is not the day. Dirk.

437
00:27:28.881 --> 00:27:30.247
The word has it you're hiring.

438
00:27:30.315 --> 00:27:32.784
Cowboys. not criminals.

439
00:27:33.952 --> 00:27:35.511
I can't stop him.

440
00:27:35.821 --> 00:27:36.821
You can.

441
00:27:38.023 --> 00:27:40.618
Jimmy's the only
family I have left.

442
00:27:41.026 --> 00:27:43.860
The favor's to me. not to him.

443
00:27:44.997 --> 00:27:46.295
Please.

444
00:27:48.634 --> 00:27:50.034
Please.

445
00:27:54.273 --> 00:27:56.037
We're gonna do
this my way. all right?

446
00:27:56.141 --> 00:27:58.076
- You understand? My way.
- Yeah.

447
00:27:58.310 --> 00:28:02.543
I remember when your way was the only
way. and the world was better for that.

448
00:28:04.183 --> 00:28:05.310
- Hello. Governor.
- John.

449
00:28:05.384 --> 00:28:06.408
How are you?

450
00:28:07.519 --> 00:28:08.885
Thank you.

451
00:28:10.722 --> 00:28:12.190
Jamie did well at the hearing.

452
00:28:12.291 --> 00:28:14.636
Yeah. well. it's easy to do well
when the outcome's decided.

453
00:28:14.660 --> 00:28:18.392
I couldn't hit it if he didn't tee it
up. and my offer still stands. John.

454
00:28:18.497 --> 00:28:20.022
Yeah. well...

455
00:28:20.232 --> 00:28:22.667
I don't want him in politics.

456
00:28:22.734 --> 00:28:24.430
He's already in politics.

457
00:28:24.536 --> 00:28:27.005
Yeah. with a
constituency of one.

458
00:28:27.506 --> 00:28:28.906
(LAUGHS)

459
00:28:30.676 --> 00:28:32.941
How concerned should I be
about this issue on the Res?

460
00:28:35.013 --> 00:28:37.573
It's a new chief
showing off for his voters.

461
00:28:37.683 --> 00:28:39.549
We've all done it.

462
00:28:42.187 --> 00:28:44.622
- (CROWD APPLAUDS)
- Well.

463
00:28:45.457 --> 00:28:47.619
we should schedule a lunch.

464
00:28:49.595 --> 00:28:51.427
I could use a lunch.

465
00:28:51.530 --> 00:28:53.863
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

466
00:29:09.881 --> 00:29:11.782
AUCTIONEER: <i>Sold it
to you. 135. sold it. 135.</i>

467
00:29:11.883 --> 00:29:13.883
- Up top there. bidder number 12.
- (CATTLE LOWING)

468
00:29:28.433 --> 00:29:29.433
You were right.

469
00:29:29.835 --> 00:29:30.996
They're building a city.

470
00:29:32.804 --> 00:29:34.295
Goodnight. Daddy.

471
00:29:35.140 --> 00:29:37.974
Goodnight. sweetheart.
Good to have you home.

472
00:30:13.979 --> 00:30:16.141
(CLICKING LIPS)

473
00:30:16.348 --> 00:30:19.216
(CLICKING TONGUE)

474
00:30:19.318 --> 00:30:21.514
That's it.

475
00:30:21.620 --> 00:30:24.180
Come on. That's it.

476
00:30:29.127 --> 00:30:32.825
That's it. That's it. buddy.

477
00:30:33.131 --> 00:30:35.191
Got tiger stripes on his legs.

478
00:30:36.702 --> 00:30:38.466
You know what that
means. don't you?

479
00:30:38.537 --> 00:30:40.802
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

480
00:30:40.872 --> 00:30:43.137
- Spanish blood.
- Pure.

481
00:30:44.309 --> 00:30:46.972
One of his ancestors
probably bucked a conquistador

482
00:30:47.045 --> 00:30:48.138
and took to the hills.

483
00:30:49.147 --> 00:30:51.912
You manage to break his spirit.
no horse will serve you better.

484
00:30:52.718 --> 00:30:54.812
He'll serve me just
fine with spirit intact.

485
00:30:55.620 --> 00:30:57.350
Yeah.

486
00:30:57.422 --> 00:30:59.823
I used to think the
same thing at your age.

487
00:31:00.692 --> 00:31:02.251
Hope you prove me wrong.

488
00:31:04.629 --> 00:31:06.069
I didn't know them
were your cattle.

489
00:31:06.832 --> 00:31:08.630
Would it have made a difference?

490
00:31:13.271 --> 00:31:15.672
You don't want to be on
the wrong side of this. son.

491
00:31:15.741 --> 00:31:18.074
Yeah. well. the list of
things I don't want is endless.

492
00:31:18.176 --> 00:31:19.940
You telling me what
to do is one of them.

493
00:31:20.045 --> 00:31:21.285
I'm not telling you what to do.

494
00:31:21.346 --> 00:31:23.178
I just don't want
you to get in trouble.

495
00:31:23.448 --> 00:31:27.249
Well. if I'd have known there was
sides. I wouldn't have been there at all.

496
00:31:31.256 --> 00:31:35.284
Good Lord. even here the
world just keeps on coming.

497
00:31:36.428 --> 00:31:38.522
KAYCE: Rough week. huh?

