were women. Lee?

750
00:50:41.906 --> 00:50:42.965
I know.

751
00:50:44.575 --> 00:50:46.373
(BOTH GRUNT)

752
00:50:50.180 --> 00:50:51.409
BETH: Hey. cowboy.

753
00:50:57.221 --> 00:50:59.850
Last time I saw you.
that was high and tight.

754
00:51:02.626 --> 00:51:03.719
How's Mr. Daniel?

755
00:51:03.928 --> 00:51:05.692
(CLICKS TONGUE)

756
00:51:05.763 --> 00:51:07.288
Good for you.

757
00:51:08.098 --> 00:51:09.910
Yeah. you're the only one
who shares that opinion.

758
00:51:09.934 --> 00:51:11.545
That's 'cause I'm the only
one who got to know him.

759
00:51:11.569 --> 00:51:13.435
(LAUGHS)

760
00:51:13.537 --> 00:51:14.800
What are you doing here?

761
00:51:16.140 --> 00:51:18.735
Closure. I guess. You?

762
00:51:18.876 --> 00:51:20.367
Penance.

763
00:51:20.444 --> 00:51:22.106
Not sure you'll find that here.

764
00:51:22.212 --> 00:51:25.182
Penance you earn.
Closure you find.

765
00:51:25.249 --> 00:51:27.411
Look somewhere
else. and you might.

766
00:51:29.386 --> 00:51:32.914
Hey. Kayce. let's
go. Grab a horse.

767
00:51:33.023 --> 00:51:36.050
(SIGHS) Any
chance you'd join us?

768
00:51:37.394 --> 00:51:38.919
I don't get near
those fucking things.

769
00:51:44.802 --> 00:51:46.896
- Yah!
- Move it!

770
00:51:46.971 --> 00:51:48.735
(MEN SHOUTING AND WHISTLING)

771
00:51:48.806 --> 00:51:50.604
- (BUFFALO SNORTING)
- (HORSES NEIGHING)

772
00:51:52.576 --> 00:51:55.774
(RANCHERS SHOUTING)

773
00:52:01.986 --> 00:52:03.750
Let me do it. Grandpa.

774
00:52:03.821 --> 00:52:04.982
- Can you do it?
- Yeah.

775
00:52:05.089 --> 00:52:06.648
Hi-yah!

776
00:52:08.158 --> 00:52:10.753
This horse ain't got any go.

777
00:52:10.828 --> 00:52:12.922
He's got some go. Hold on.

778
00:52:13.163 --> 00:52:14.631
I'll get him going for you.

779
00:52:14.698 --> 00:52:15.825
Race you. Yah!

780
00:52:15.933 --> 00:52:17.299
Yah!

781
00:52:21.605 --> 00:52:22.605
(CLICKS TONGUE)

782
00:52:22.673 --> 00:52:23.673
Yah!

783
00:52:24.174 --> 00:52:25.267
Whoo!

784
00:52:33.283 --> 00:52:35.047
Think they should hold here.

785
00:52:36.186 --> 00:52:38.621
(RANCHERS SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

786
00:52:38.689 --> 00:52:41.158
Kayce might be the only
man who can outride him.

787
00:52:44.361 --> 00:52:45.954
Just might be.

788
00:53:04.381 --> 00:53:06.509
Fish on. Tate.

789
00:53:13.057 --> 00:53:14.582
All right. buddy.

790
00:53:17.027 --> 00:53:19.656
Here. grab... Grab that rod.

791
00:53:19.730 --> 00:53:21.323
Reel him in.

792
00:53:23.233 --> 00:53:25.168
There you go. Reel it in. buddy.

793
00:53:27.237 --> 00:53:28.237
(CHUCKLES)

794
00:53:28.372 --> 00:53:29.396
Whoo!

795
00:53:30.240 --> 00:53:33.574
Lee. get my horse. Whoo!

796
00:53:33.911 --> 00:53:35.231
Little late in
the year for that.

797
00:53:38.749 --> 00:53:39.749
Got him.

798
00:53:41.351 --> 00:53:43.013
TATE: I caught a fish!

799
00:53:43.087 --> 00:53:44.715
KAYCE: Can you pull him up?

800
00:53:44.788 --> 00:53:46.313
Look at that.

801
00:53:46.390 --> 00:53:47.517
Whoo!

802
00:53:47.591 --> 00:53:49.890
That's a big one. huh?

803
00:53:49.960 --> 00:53:51.588
TATE: Yeah. LEE:
Oh. she's pretty.

804
00:53:51.695 --> 00:53:53.220
Look at that one.

805
00:53:58.368 --> 00:53:59.368
Any luck?

806
00:54:17.154 --> 00:54:18.884
Here. wait. don't touch it.

807
00:54:18.956 --> 00:54:20.049
It's kind of hot.

808
00:54:21.759 --> 00:54:22.759
Careful.

809
00:54:22.826 --> 00:54:24.624
You're gonna raise
him on a reservation?

810
00:54:25.662 --> 00:54:27.426
People do it every day.

811
00:54:28.098 --> 00:54:29.532
'Cause they have
no choice. Kayce.

812
00:54:30.467 --> 00:54:32.595
Yeah. looks like
he's ready to eat.

813
00:54:33.971 --> 00:54:35.837
It's a good day.

814
00:54:37.007 --> 00:54:39.806
Every day. just like this.

815
00:54:39.910 --> 00:54:41.538
Who are you kidding?

816
00:54:41.612 --> 00:54:43.672
Bet you haven't
fished here in years.

817
00:54:44.314 --> 00:54:47.375
Only thing we haven't done
in years is see you. Kayce.

818
00:54:47.451 --> 00:54:49.682
Well. he told me to leave.

819
00:54:49.787 --> 00:54:52.086
He told us all to leave.

820
00:54:52.189 --> 00:54:54.124
You were just the
only one who did.

821
00:54:56.193 --> 00:54:58.788
It's different. You know that.

822
00:54:59.696 --> 00:55:03.133
Right. so you're gonna raise him in
that meth-filled desert to prove a point.

823
00:55:03.467 --> 00:55:05.663
What I'm proving
you'll never understand.

824
00:55:06.003 --> 00:55:07.801
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

825
00:55:07.871 --> 00:55:09.169
(CHUCKLES)

826
00:55:09.273 --> 00:55:11.572
Shit. I miss being young.

827
00:55:11.642 --> 00:55:14.669
You wake up in the morning. and
you just keep right on dreaming. huh?

828
00:55:16.446 --> 00:55:19.939
You're a 38-year-old bachelor
living in your father's house.

829
00:55:20.017 --> 00:55:22.577
working 100-hour weeks
for a nibble of his approval.

830
00:55:22.653 --> 00:55:25.122
Is that the dream. Lee?

831
00:55:25.589 --> 00:55:27.683
Sure as shit ain't mine.

832
00:55:34.198 --> 00:55:35.689
- Hey.
- (LAUGHS)

833
00:55:35.833 --> 00:55:37.131
TATE: Hey!

834
00:55:37.201 --> 00:55:39.136
Don't throw things at my dad.

835
00:55:39.203 --> 00:55:40.280
- Hey. hey. hey. hey.
- Whoa!

836
00:55:40.304 --> 00:55:41.363
- Oh.
- Fucker.

837
00:55:41.471 --> 00:55:42.803
- Tate!
- Whoa!

838
00:55:42.973 --> 00:55:45.306
(LAUGHS)

839
00:55:46.510 --> 00:55:48.172
(LAUGHING) It's okay. buddy.

840
00:55:50.247 --> 00:55:51.647
We're just brothers
arguing. man.

841
00:55:51.715 --> 00:55:53.047
Nobody's mad. okay?

842
00:55:53.150 --> 00:55:54.641
It's all right.

843
00:55:55.919 --> 00:55:58.479
You gonna tell me there's
no fight in that blood?

844
00:56:00.057 --> 00:56:02.049
He's right though.

845
00:56:02.159 --> 00:56:03.422
It is a good day.

846
00:56:06.063 --> 00:56:07.895
He said "fucker."

847
00:56:07.998 --> 00:56:10.024
(LAUGHING)

848
00:56:15.939 --> 00:56:17.840
You got green for water.

849
00:56:17.908 --> 00:56:19.672
Blue is sewage. yellow for gas.

850
00:56:19.743 --> 00:56:21.678
Driveways are marked in pink

851
00:56:21.745 --> 00:56:24.180
and corner buildings in red.

852
00:56:24.414 --> 00:56:26.349
If I were to dam the river

853
00:56:27.951 --> 00:56:29.852
I'd do it right there
around the bend.

854
00:56:30.687 --> 00:56:32.553
That's where they're doing it.

855
00:56:34.124 --> 00:56:35.854
That's your property upstream?

856
00:56:38.896 --> 00:56:40.762
Now. I'm not gonna lie to you.

857
00:56:40.864 --> 00:56:43.424
There's gonna be a
severe impact to your land.

858
00:56:43.533 --> 00:56:45.297
Erosion's my biggest concern.

859
00:56:48.572 --> 00:56:52.100
My biggest concern is a
subdivision sucking on our river.

860
00:56:52.209 --> 00:56:54.235
There's nothing you can do.

861
00:56:54.311 --> 00:56:56.678
On their land. it's their river.

862
00:56:56.947 --> 00:56:59.075
I mean. I can't stop
the river from flowing.

863
00:57:08.558 --> 00:57:10.618
I don't want you
to stop it. Ron.

864
00:57:10.727 --> 00:57:12.320
I want you to move it.

865
00:57:24.341 --> 00:57:25.707
How's it going over there?

866
00:57:25.776 --> 00:57:27.220
Oh. hey. we got to
make the dressing.

867
00:57:27.244 --> 00:57:28.268
Oh. okay. I'll make it.

868
00:57:32.649 --> 00:57:34.174
How could you give
him a D. Monica?

869
00:57:34.284 --> 00:57:35.479
He's your nephew.

870
00:57:35.585 --> 00:57:37.918
The D was a gift. believe me.

871
00:57:38.522 --> 00:57:39.751
What can I say?

872
00:57:39.823 --> 00:57:42.657
Math is not his
thing. like his father.

873
00:57:42.759 --> 00:57:46.161
Well. he better make it his thing.
or he's gonna end up like his father.

874
00:57:47.497 --> 00:57:49.728
He's my brother. I can say it.

875
00:57:50.000 --> 00:57:52.595
When I get my steers.
I'm gonna take one.

876
00:57:52.669 --> 00:57:55.036
and carve out a porterhouse
the size of a radiator.

877
00:57:55.138 --> 00:57:57.266
(BOTH LAUGH)

878
00:57:57.341 --> 00:57:58.832
They divvying up the cattle?

879
00:58:02.045 --> 00:58:05.538
You don't like it. maybe you
shouldn't have rounded them up.

880
00:58:07.517 --> 00:58:09.110
They ain't yours to divvy.

881
00:58:13.824 --> 00:58:15.850
What is that one?

882
00:58:18.195 --> 00:58:19.788
It's a Silver Star.

883
00:58:20.697 --> 00:58:22.495
You got one of those?

884
00:58:24.968 --> 00:58:27.631
What do you have
to do to win one?

885
00:58:27.704 --> 00:58:29.570
You got to kill someone
to get one of those.

886
00:58:30.807 --> 00:58:32.036
Ain't that right. Kayce?

887
00:58:34.411 --> 00:58:36.004
What about that one?

888
00:58:39.016 --> 00:58:40.177
That's the Navy Cross.

889
00:58:41.852 --> 00:58:44.048
You wouldn't believe what
I had to do to get that one.

890
00:58:44.721 --> 00:58:46.690
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

891
00:58:51.561 --> 00:58:53.052
What's he doing here?

892
00:58:58.268 --> 00:58:59.759
Well. I hope I'm not intruding.

893
00:58:59.870 --> 00:59:02.032
Of course not. but my
grandfather's not here.

894
00:59:02.105 --> 00:59:04.074
Well. I'm not here to
see your grandfather.

895
00:59:07.077 --> 00:59:10.070
I want to thank you for
helping the other day.

896
00:59:10.180 --> 00:59:12.206
I don't know your father.

897
00:59:12.282 --> 00:59:15.275
I hope it didn't put you in
an uncomfortable position.

898
00:59:16.586 --> 00:59:18.418
Well. if you plan on
keeping his cattle.

899
00:59:18.522 --> 00:59:20.115
you'll get to know
him real well.

900
00:59:20.223 --> 00:59:22.385
(CHUCKLES)

901
00:59:22.459 --> 00:59:26.419
Those are bargaining
chips. a means to an end.

902
00:59:26.530 --> 00:59:30.626
Politicians are like crabs. We
move sideways to go forward.

903
00:59:30.734 --> 00:59:32.414
Well. that won't get
you too far with him.

904
00:59:33.737 --> 00:59:35.706
An honest man?

905
00:59:35.772 --> 00:59:37.683
He says he'll do something.
you're not gonna stop him.

906
00:59:37.707 --> 00:59:40.108
if you call that honest.

907
00:59:40.210 --> 00:59:42.236
I do.

908
00:59:42.312 --> 00:59:44.781
It's a rare thing these days.

909
00:59:44.881 --> 00:59:47.407
What do you want from me?

910
00:59:47.484 --> 00:59:49.953
To help me

911
00:59:50.053 --> 00:59:53.751
understand the man
I'm negotiating with.

912
00:59:56.193 --> 00:59:59.561
Well. he's reasonable
till he's provoked.

913
01:00:00.931 --> 01:00:03.127
Then reason
don't factor in at all.

914
01:00:05.569 --> 01:00:08.596
Doubt that helps you.
but that's who he is.

915
01:00:09.139 --> 01:00:10.732
That helps.

916
01:00:12.809 --> 01:00:14.744
Thank you for your time.

917
01:00:15.112 --> 01:00:16.603
Have a good evening.

918
01:00:24.321 --> 01:00:25.321
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

919
01:00:25.422 --> 01:00:26.947
(CLICKS LIPS)

920
01:00:28.825 --> 01:00:31.056
You're not joining him?

921
01:00:31.128 --> 01:00:33.688
You didn't ask me here to hunt.

922
01:00:33.797 --> 01:00:36.130
I'm here to talk cattle.

923
01:00:36.233 --> 01:00:38.464
They don't belong to you.

924
01:00:38.535 --> 01:00:40.629
They don't belong to you either.

925
01:00:40.704 --> 01:00:42.696
They belong to the people now.

926
01:00:42.806 --> 01:00:44.775
JOHN: Every one of
them wears a brand.

927
01:00:44.841 --> 01:00:46.639
If anybody tries to
move them off the Res...

928
01:00:46.710 --> 01:00:48.474
They'll never leave the Res.

929
01:00:48.545 --> 01:00:51.606
We'll use them to raise
calves. wear our brand.

930
01:00:52.682 --> 01:00:56.642
I understand your position. Thomas.
and what you think you need to do.

931
01:00:56.720 --> 01:01:00.157
but I won't allow you to make
victims of the people who elected me

932
01:01:00.257 --> 01:01:03.193
just to appease the
people who elected you.

933
01:01:03.293 --> 01:01:05.819
Your people don't know
the concept of victim.

934
01:01:09.299 --> 01:01:12.064
Let's keep this about cattle.

935
01:01:12.169 --> 01:01:16.504
If you act like a thief.
Thomas. I will treat you like one.

936
01:01:16.573 --> 01:01:19.702
How can you stand there on a
ranch the size of Rhode Island

937
01:01:19.809 --> 01:01:22.745
and accuse me of theft?

938
01:01:22.846 --> 01:01:25.543
Is this your idea of respect?

939
01:01:25.649 --> 01:01:27.811
Letting some crippled old
man ride his lame horse

940
01:01:27.884 --> 01:01:29.876
out toward your
half-tame buffalo

941
01:01:29.986 --> 01:01:32.512
so he can pretend to be something
we haven't been in a century?

942
01:01:41.198 --> 01:01:43.292
Whoo!

943
01:01:44.334 --> 01:01:46.326
Look what you've reduced us to.

944
01:01:46.403 --> 01:01:47.928
(CLICKS TONGUE)

945
01:01:55.412 --> 01:01:56.846
Here's another one.

946
01:01:56.913 --> 01:01:59.712
(HEN CLUCKING)

947
01:01:59.783 --> 01:02:01.877
You lay everywhere but the coop.

948
01:02:06.022 --> 01:02:08.116
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

949
01:02:12.529 --> 01:02:13.724
(SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE)

950
01:02:13.797 --> 01:02:16.028
(SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE)

951
01:02:23.540 --> 01:02:24.735
Backstraps.

952
01:02:24.808 --> 01:02:26.777
- Staying for dinner?
- Can't.

953
01:02:26.876 --> 01:02:29.277
Just need a few words
with this young buck here.

954
01:02:29.379 --> 01:02:31.280
Can you give us a minute?

955
01:02:31.381 --> 01:02:34.613
If you can say it to him.
you can say it to me.

956
01:02:34.718 --> 01:02:38.553
Hard to talk about you when
you're standing here. darling.

957
01:02:38.622 --> 01:02:41.592
Come on. Tate. We're
being sent to our room.

958
01:02:43.727 --> 01:02:46.663
The Nation will keep the cattle.

959
01:02:46.763 --> 01:02:49.426
Your father will try
to take them back.

960
01:02:49.532 --> 01:02:52.229
He has every right.

961
01:02:52.302 --> 01:02:57.070
We had every right to take
them. so now we will fight.

962
01:02:58.775 --> 01:03:01.244
It's his fight. not mine.

963
01:03:01.311 --> 01:03:05.806
You will be judged for
the actions of your father.

964
01:03:05.915 --> 01:03:09.317
If you do nothing. you
will be judged for that too.

965
01:03:09.419 --> 01:03:11.911
They all will.

966
01:03:11.988 --> 01:03:15.857
Maybe it's best you go
home for a while. eh?

967
01:03:15.959 --> 01:03:17.393
This is my home.

968
01:03:17.460 --> 01:03:19.793
You know what I mean.

969
01:03:22.265 --> 01:03:24.860
I've been nothing but a
friend to everybody here.

970
01:03:26.102 --> 01:03:29.095
If somebody wants me to leave.
you can tell them to come make me.

971
01:03:29.172 --> 01:03:32.472
Pretty silly thing to
say on a reservation.

972
01:03:33.943 --> 01:03:39.007
I don't ask much. but
I'm asking you this.

973
01:03:39.115 --> 01:03:41.016
Go home.

974
01:03:41.117 --> 01:03:44.610
Take care of my granddaughter.

975
01:03:44.688 --> 01:03:47.487
Be good to that boy.

976
01:03:47.590 --> 01:03:54.394
Until they find a cure for human
nature. a man must stand with his people.

977
01:03:58.635 --> 01:04:00.160
And we are not your people.

978
01:04:17.420 --> 01:04:19.548
RIP: Hey. Hey. Jimmy!

979
01:04:19.656 --> 01:04:21.249
Let's go. You're late.

980
01:04:21.358 --> 01:04:23.623
Let's go. You're late.

981
01:04:24.894 --> 01:04:27.864
- You know how to ride a horse?
- Uh...

982
01:04:27.931 --> 01:04:29.729
Figures. Come here.
Give me your shit.

983
01:04:29.833 --> 01:04:31.699
Let's go. That there is Ron.

984
01:04:31.768 --> 01:04:33.999
You do whatever the
hell he asks you to do.

985
01:04:34.871 --> 01:04:37.397
Come on. get on.
Get on the horse.

986
01:04:37.507 --> 01:04:38.668
I don't...

987
01:04:40.176 --> 01:04:41.769
Get on the horse. Jimmy.

988
01:04:45.682 --> 01:04:47.722
Pull the reins to stop.
Kick him in the belly to go.

989
01:04:48.418 --> 01:04:49.943
All right. let's move.

990
01:04:58.695 --> 01:05:00.061
Both in one night?

991
01:05:02.265 --> 01:05:04.461
Everyone's forgotten
who runs this valley.

992
01:05:05.802 --> 01:05:07.600
So this is how you remind them?

993
01:05:08.772 --> 01:05:10.365
This is not the
way to remind them.

994
01:05:10.440 --> 01:05:12.432
It's a bad idea.

995
01:05:12.542 --> 01:05:14.204
We don't choose
the way. little brother.

996
01:05:16.546 --> 01:05:19.038
(HELICOPTER POWERING UP)

997
01:05:55.018 --> 01:05:58.182
TATE: Dad. I'm
the fastest runner.

998
01:05:58.288 --> 01:06:00.018
I'm bucking. I'm bucking.

999
01:06:01.491 --> 01:06:03.585
And he falls.

1000
01:06:03.660 --> 01:06:04.889
(THUDS AND LAUGHS)

1001
01:06:07.297 --> 01:06:10.267
<i>Home</i>

1002
01:06:10.333 --> 01:06:15.670
<i>A candle you can
hold. you're not alone</i>

1003
01:06:19.609 --> 01:06:23.273
<i>Home</i>

1004
01:06:23.346 --> 01:06:29.183
<i>So far away. come on home</i>

1005
01:06:32.355 --> 01:06:35.519
